text: Hi, I'm Shannon, and I'm a 24-year-old AAPI content creator based in Miami, Florida. I am originally from New York in the Bronx, and I fell in love with content creation at the early age of eight or nine. And it's really started when I got my first phone with a camera, and I just fell in love with being able to capture photos and videos and being able to share them with my friends and family, and just putting everything together to make a storyline, and just, I, I just love it so much. I think if you really go back to my roots, I started really early in middle school and high school with experimenting with my YouTube channel and making little cute videos on there. I would send them to my friends, and then they'd send them to their friends, and it was just, it was such a surreal feeling of growing my own personal brand and, like, community. I've always wanted that close-knit bond with me being the creator and people in the audience being my viewers, and I, I've always been like that. I think if you really look at my middle school and high school transcript, I believe I took all art, uh, extracurriculars, so I took fashion design, interior design, photography. I fell in love with cinematography and film at the same time, which I took a class for. And I also took art. I took Art 2. There was a lot of art, extra art curriculars that I took, and by the end of my high school graduation, I graduated with extra art curriculars. (laughs) So, I think that was a sign that this was really meant for me. And after I got into college, I got into nursing school, but then I flunked out, and I honestly took it as a sign that maybe it wasn't meant for me and that I should really pursue content creation full-time. So, here I am, college dropout (laughs), and I honestly couldn't have been happier. It has been really, really hard trying to find my place in the content creator world, but I wouldn't have it any other way. I would not regret it one bit. If you were to fast-forward and I am old and wrinkly at 65 and you ask me what my biggest regret would be, it would probably be that I wished that I would have started sooner and not when I was after college and just not really figuring out what I wanted to do. And I think that this is the best job and best career path for me in general, because I'm just super passionate about it. I always prioritize quality over quantity, because I see a lot of creators that just are in it for the money, and I'm not like that. I love, love, love, love just creating for people to relate and just find their own stories within my own. And yeah.
